==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Calibration
<hw>Cal`ibra"*tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The process of
estimating the caliber a tube, as of a thermometer tube, in order to
graduate it to a scale of degrees; also, more generally, the
determination of the true value of the spaces in any graduated
instrument.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calice</ent>⟦br⟧
